# Figma console log

When working on scripts in this project (anything under `scripts/`), **always read the Figma console log** so debugging is seamless.

- **Log file**: `figma-console.log` (project root). Written by the console bridge when `npm run dev` is running.
- **When**: At the start of script-related work, and when debugging plugin/script errors.
- **How**: Use `Read` with `offset`/`limit` or `Grep` if the file is large; otherwise read the whole file.

This project keeps the log un-ignored so the agent can read it; it is not committed (see `.git/info/exclude`).
